# Anti-AI-Slop Rule

> LLMs converge toward generic designs because high-probability tokens dominate sampling.
> This rule exists to break that convergence in ALL frontend output.

## When generating ANY frontend code:

### Typography
1. **NEVER** use Inter, Roboto, Arial, Open Sans, Lato or system fonts as the primary choice
2. **NEVER** use generic serifs (Times New Roman, Georgia, Garamond, Palatino) — if a serif is
   needed, use only Fraunces, Gambarino, Editorial New, Instrument Serif
3. **NEVER** use a serif in dashboards / software UIs — only sans-serif pairings (Geist + Geist Mono,
   Satoshi + JetBrains Mono)
4. **NEVER** generate an H1 with more than 2-3 lines — use `max-w-5xl/6xl` + `clamp()` to force horizontal wrap
5. **ALWAYS** use Geist, Outfit, Cabinet Grotesk or Satoshi for display in premium contexts

### Color
6. **NEVER** use purple gradients on a white background — AI slop cliché number 1
7. **NEVER** use neon/outer glow `box-shadow` — use inner borders or tinted shadows
8. **NEVER** use pure `#000000` — use Off-Black, Zinc-950 or Charcoal
9. **NEVER** use an oversaturated accent (saturation > 80%)
10. **NEVER** mix warm and cool grays in the same project
11. **ALWAYS** limit to 1 accent color per output
12. **ALWAYS** use neutrals (Zinc/Slate) as the base + 1 contrasting accent

### Layout
13. **NEVER** replicate the "Vercel template" layout (hero split left/right, generic bento grid, 3 identical cards)
14. **NEVER** use 3 identical cards horizontally in a feature row — use a zig-zag 2-col, asymmetric grid, or horizontal scroll
15. **NEVER** use `h-screen` for hero — always `min-h-[100dvh]` (iOS Safari bug)
16. **NEVER** use flexbox math with `calc()` — always CSS Grid for multi-column
17. **NEVER** center the Hero when visual ambition > 4 (variance) — force Split Screen or Asymmetric

### Content (Jane Doe Effect)
18. **NEVER** use generic names: "John Doe", "Sarah Chan", "Jack Su" — invent realistic creative names
19. **NEVER** use generic companies: "Acme", "Nexus", "SmartFlow" — invent contextual brand names
20. **NEVER** use fake numbers: `99.99%`, `50%`, `1234567` — use organic ones (`47.2%`, `+1 (312) 847-1928`)
21. **NEVER** use AI copywriting: "Elevate", "Seamless", "Unleash", "Next-Gen", "Game-changer", "Delve", "Tapestry"
22. **NEVER** use meta-labels: "SECTION 01", "QUESTION 05", "ABOUT US"
23. **NEVER** use filler UI: "Scroll to explore", "Swipe down", scroll arrows, bouncing chevrons
24. **NEVER** use broken Unsplash — use `https://picsum.photos/seed/{string}/W/H`

### Components
25. **NEVER** use shadcn/ui in its generic default state — customize radii, colors, shadows
26. **NEVER** use Lucide/Feather as the only icon option — use Phosphor, Radix, Heroicons
27. **NEVER** mix stroke-widths from different icons — standardize on 1.5 or 2.0
28. **NEVER** use emojis in code, markup, alt text — use icons or SVG primitives

### Performance
29. **NEVER** animate `top`, `left`, `width` or `height` — only `transform` and `opacity`
30. **NEVER** apply `backdrop-blur` on scrolling containers — only on fixed/sticky
31. **NEVER** apply grain/noise on scrolling containers — only on `fixed inset-0 pointer-events-none`
32. **NEVER** use `window.addEventListener('scroll')` — use IntersectionObserver or Framer `whileInView`

### Meta
33. **NEVER** repeat the same aesthetic choice from a previous generation IN THE SAME SESSION (second-order anti-convergence)
34. **NEVER** create incomplete output: `// ... rest of code`, `// TODO`, "for brevity" → activate `output-enforcement`
35. **ALWAYS** commit to an intentional aesthetic direction before coding (trigger `aesthetic-modes` if needed)
36. **ALWAYS** use CSS variables for design tokens
37. **ALWAYS** check deps in `package.json` before importing libs (framer-motion, gsap, etc.)
38. If the project has brand assets → use them as the foundation
39. If it doesn't → create an original direction that serves the context
40. **Complexity matching:** maximalist design = elaborate code; minimalist design = restraint and precision

> **For a deep-dive:** `skills/aesthetic-boost` (compact primer), `skills/taste-design-dials` (3-dial system),
> `skills/aesthetic-modes` (Editorial / Brutalist / Soft modes).
